<br>
However, most developers like to move onto something new after awhile... they don't like fixing all the bugs in a list for a specific part of a product, and then moving on to the next part of the product and doing it again.  They'd much rather create new code.<br>
<br>
That's not to say that there aren't people who just like to fix bugs: there definitely are.  I worked with an insanely bright developer a few years ago who truly loved fixing bugs -- he thought it was far more challenging than any new development project was.<br>
<br>
